title: Grateful Dead Live at Euphoria Ballroom on 1970-07-14
lineage: SBD > MR > Cass > DAT > CDR > EAC > SHN
description: Don't Ease Me In, Friend Of The Devil, Dire Wolf, Dark Hollow, Candyman, Black Peter, How Long Blues, Deep Elem Blues, Cumberland Blues*, New Speedway Boogie* The Frozen Logger, Casey Jones, El Paso, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Easy Wind, Me & My Uncle, Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Cryptical Envelopement-> Cosmic Charlie, Good Lovin'%, Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text:
Acoustic Set It seems as though nobody wants to give this show a chance.  And while the electric set is plagued with mix and buzzing problems, the acoustic set, I believe, is still a great listen, with some great banter.  

I would put the acoustic set in my keep list without a doubt.

Follow the tour:
gratefuldeadlive.blogspot.com

How long, How Long Make it past the audience Don't Ease 
and I agree with  reviewer August West 
the acoustic set is a "GREAT LISTEN"
with a rare How Long Blues
and a guest jam with David Crosby

Here's the quote of the day:
Charlie Daniels: The only two things that matter are 'the grace of God and the United States military'

Electric Set:
Missing:  Frozen Logger
Casey jones- a tad distant 
EL PASO- Bob takes his time with the lyrics (unique)
China>Rider- oh really good! The sound is top shelf
laid back,compared to 72 Alvin & Chipmunk versions
Easy Wind-ouch
Me & My Uncle-slow like El Paso
(request a cowboy transfusion) 
That's it for the Other One- 1970 thick-nice drums
Explosive TOO jam
Both sets a little scarce on the Pigpen
(especially with cut in Easy Wind)
4.5 Acoustic
3.5 Electric
Can anybody explain why this source has 45,000 views and the other 15,000 views
but almost all of the commentary 
is on the other source?
I don't detect a major sound difference?
Can't go wrong with Uncle John's as an encore.
